The paper deals with the problem of computing public transit traffic assignments in a multi-modal setting, which involves algorithmic challenges and requires careful algorithm engineering. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to algorithms and optimization, such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a state-of-the-art assignment algorithm and a recently proposed approach (ULTRA), which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also involves extensive evaluation of the algorithm, which could fall under sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
